## Final Note from the CTO

Every role in this document was designed backward from the learning science, not forward from a generic startup org chart. The synthesis is unambiguous: the platforms that win in EdTech are not the ones with the most content — they are the ones that operationalize retrieval practice, interleaving, desirable difficulty, and intrinsic motivation at the product layer.

Each hire has a defined mandate, measurable success criteria, and a direct line to one or more of the five highest-impact features. **Scope creep is the primary execution risk** — each hire must be held to their lane, especially in the first six months.

> **Build the learning engine first. Ship the gamification layer second. Then grow.**
